Looking at the code, I can see the issue. In the Login.kt file, there's a LaunchedEffect that triggers whenever the loginState changes:

```kotlin
is Resource.Error -> {
 LaunchedEffect(loginState) {
 Toast.makeText(context, "Login Failed", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()
 }
 // ... rest of error handling
}
```

The problem is that the LoginViewModel's loginState might be persisting an error state from a previous interaction (possibly from the signup page or a previous login attempt). When the user navigates back to the login page, if the loginState is still in an error state, the LaunchedEffect will trigger and show the "Login Failed" toast immediately.

The solution is to reset the login state when the composable is first composed or when the user navigates back to it. I need to check the LoginViewModel to see if there's a method to reset the state, or add one if it doesn't exist.

